{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make payments on account optional for the self employed",
        "additional_details": "Make POA optional. Give us the choice to pay it. I always put money aside for my tax bill but have a quiet start to the year generally so I need the money that HMRC are demanding. I feel the HMRC are getting an interest free loan from the self employed.",
        "background": "Currently the self employed are expected to pay 50% of the next years tax bill based on the previous year tax. Self employed people don\u2019t earn a fixed amount therefore the payments on account is needed to pay bills.",
